WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.960 align:middle line:90%
[SQUEAKING]

00:00:01.960 --> 00:00:04.410 align:middle line:90%
[RUSTLING]

00:00:04.410 --> 00:00:08.330 align:middle line:90%
[CLICKING]

00:00:08.330 --> 00:00:11.000 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.630 align:middle line:84%
PROFESSOR: So I hope you all
have had a great spring break.

00:00:15.630 --> 00:00:21.190 align:middle line:84%
So before the break, we
talked about Dirac equation.

00:00:21.190 --> 00:00:23.490 align:middle line:90%
So we introduced the equation.

00:00:23.490 --> 00:00:30.150 align:middle line:84%
We showed that it is
Lorentz covariant.

00:00:30.150 --> 00:00:34.260 align:middle line:84%
And then we started talking
about the classical solutions

00:00:34.260 --> 00:00:40.260 align:middle line:84%
of the Dirac equation,
because the finding

00:00:40.260 --> 00:00:44.520 align:middle line:84%
the complete set of
solutions for Dirac equation

00:00:44.520 --> 00:00:50.190 align:middle line:84%
is the necessary step
for quantizing it.

00:00:50.190 --> 00:01:04.239 align:middle line:84%
So let us consider the classical
solutions of Dirac equations.

00:01:04.239 --> 00:01:09.070 align:middle line:90%


00:01:09.070 --> 00:01:12.010 align:middle line:84%
And recall the Dirac equation
is given by the following.

00:01:12.010 --> 00:01:17.220 align:middle line:90%


00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:19.270 align:middle line:90%
So this gamma matrices--

00:01:19.270 --> 00:01:23.130 align:middle line:84%
so these gamma matrices
are 4x4 matrices,

00:01:23.130 --> 00:01:27.820 align:middle line:84%
and psi is a four
complex vector.

00:01:27.820 --> 00:01:30.840 align:middle line:84%
And we already just
from setting up

00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:34.110 align:middle line:84%
the Dirac equation and the
properties of the gamma

00:01:34.110 --> 00:01:40.960 align:middle line:84%
matrices that this
should have solutions

00:01:40.960 --> 00:01:47.500 align:middle line:84%
proportional to plane
wave with k square equal

00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:50.170 align:middle line:90%
to minus m square.

00:01:50.170 --> 00:01:58.600 align:middle line:84%
So our goal is to
find the pre-factors.

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:02.180 align:middle line:84%
So here, we separate into
two kinds of solutions.

00:02:02.180 --> 00:02:04.060 align:middle line:90%
So this just reminds you--

00:02:04.060 --> 00:02:07.850 align:middle line:84%
we discussed that at the
end of last lecture--

00:02:07.850 --> 00:02:11.560 align:middle line:84%
we call uk corresponding
to the positive.

00:02:11.560 --> 00:02:21.930 align:middle line:84%
So we always take k to have
positive time component.

00:02:21.930 --> 00:02:25.770 align:middle line:84%
And so this is the
positive energy solution.

00:02:25.770 --> 00:02:29.710 align:middle line:84%
Then we have also so-called
negative energy solution.

00:02:29.710 --> 00:02:31.440 align:middle line:90%
So these are just names.

00:02:31.440 --> 00:02:34.890 align:middle line:84%
Does not really means that
they have positive energy

00:02:34.890 --> 00:02:36.610 align:middle line:90%
or negative energy.

00:02:36.610 --> 00:02:40.800 align:middle line:84%
It just means that
the sign here.

00:02:40.800 --> 00:02:46.630 align:middle line:84%
So now, if you plug this
into the Dirac equation,

00:02:46.630 --> 00:02:49.740 align:middle line:84%
and then you get the
algebraic equation for u.

00:02:49.740 --> 00:02:52.020 align:middle line:84%
You get the algebraic
equation for u,

00:02:52.020 --> 00:03:03.332 align:middle line:84%
and then you find i k slash
m u equal to 0, and the i k

00:03:03.332 --> 00:03:08.160 align:middle line:90%
slash plus m v equal to 0.

00:03:08.160 --> 00:03:12.150 align:middle line:84%
So u and v satisfy
those equations.

00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:21.120 align:middle line:84%
And so I suppose you're already
familiar with the rotation--

00:03:21.120 --> 00:03:22.150 align:middle line:90%
so this k slash.

00:03:22.150 --> 00:03:27.890 align:middle line:90%


00:03:27.890 --> 00:03:29.600 align:middle line:84%
So those equations,
in principle,

00:03:29.600 --> 00:03:31.010 align:middle line:90%
you can just solve them.

00:03:31.010 --> 00:03:33.230 align:middle line:84%
So these are just
linear equations.

00:03:33.230 --> 00:03:39.500 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, in principle,
you can just solve them.

00:03:39.500 --> 00:03:44.660 align:middle line:84%
But still there are tricks
how we solve them so

00:03:44.660 --> 00:03:47.510 align:middle line:90%
that it's mostly transparent.

00:03:47.510 --> 00:03:50.225 align:middle line:84%
So there are two methods
of finding the u and k.

00:03:50.225 --> 00:03:52.990 align:middle line:90%


00:03:52.990 --> 00:03:55.810 align:middle line:84%
So one method is we first
go to the rest frame--

00:03:55.810 --> 00:04:00.850 align:middle line:90%


00:04:00.850 --> 00:04:08.990 align:middle line:84%
say we take k mu, say, to
have 0 spatial momentum.

00:04:08.990 --> 00:04:15.080 align:middle line:84%
And then the k mu will
be just equal to m 0.

00:04:15.080 --> 00:04:18.709 align:middle line:84%
So in this case, those equations
become particularly simple.

00:04:18.709 --> 00:04:21.769 align:middle line:84%
And also before we
solve them, actually we

00:04:21.769 --> 00:04:26.660 align:middle line:84%
should also specify the gamma
matrices we need to use.

00:04:26.660 --> 00:04:34.640 align:middle line:84%
So the gamma matrices we will
use is given by the following.

00:04:34.640 --> 00:04:36.395 align:middle line:84%
Again, each are
the 2 by 2 block.

00:04:36.395 --> 00:04:51.220 align:middle line:90%


00:04:51.220 --> 00:04:54.980 align:middle line:84%
So this is the gamma
matrices we are going to use.

00:04:54.980 --> 00:04:57.580 align:middle line:84%
And as we discussed
before, there

00:04:57.580 --> 00:05:01.390 align:middle line:84%
are many, many different
choices of gamma matrices.

00:05:01.390 --> 00:05:08.300 align:middle line:84%
And some of them are
convenient for certain purpose.

00:05:08.300 --> 00:05:10.310 align:middle line:84%
And as we will see,
this one actually

00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:14.120 align:middle line:84%
makes the non-relativistic
limit more manifest.

00:05:14.120 --> 00:05:20.710 align:middle line:84%
So it's conveniently reduced
to non-relativistic limit.

00:05:20.710 --> 00:05:25.030 align:middle line:84%
And so in the rest frame,
those equations simplify--

00:05:25.030 --> 00:05:29.620 align:middle line:84%
essentially, u just becomes
the eigenvalue equations

00:05:29.620 --> 00:05:31.450 align:middle line:90%
for gamma 0.

00:05:31.450 --> 00:05:37.240 align:middle line:84%
So you find-- say,
this equation for u--

00:05:37.240 --> 00:05:40.400 align:middle line:90%


00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:46.510 align:middle line:84%
so let's denote to the
rest frame by 0, and then--

00:05:46.510 --> 00:05:53.290 align:middle line:84%
so the equation for u just
becomes this in the rest frame,

00:05:53.290 --> 00:05:59.490 align:middle line:90%
and the v given by this.

00:05:59.490 --> 00:06:05.080 align:middle line:84%
So essentially, this is just
corresponding-- essentially,

00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:06.610 align:middle line:90%
you see the u and v--

00:06:06.610 --> 00:06:11.710 align:middle line:84%
u0 and v0 just corresponding
to eigenvalues of gamma 0,

00:06:11.710 --> 00:06:14.650 align:middle line:84%
because this is gamma 0
times u gives you a constant.

00:06:14.650 --> 00:06:17.525 align:middle line:84%
It can be-- move that constant
to the right-hand side-- it

00:06:17.525 --> 00:06:19.150 align:middle line:84%
just looks like an
eigenvalue equation.

00:06:19.150 --> 00:06:21.980 align:middle line:90%


00:06:21.980 --> 00:06:24.350 align:middle line:90%
And so you can just easily--

00:06:24.350 --> 00:06:27.830 align:middle line:84%
you can plug this in and easily
solve them, which we already

00:06:27.830 --> 00:06:30.920 align:middle line:90%
discussed last time.

00:06:30.920 --> 00:06:33.050 align:middle line:84%
So for example,
you find that there

00:06:33.050 --> 00:06:34.800 align:middle line:90%
are two independent equations.

00:06:34.800 --> 00:06:37.610 align:middle line:90%
So this is a 4x4 matrix.

00:06:37.610 --> 00:06:40.160 align:middle line:90%
So gamma 0 is a 4x4 matrix.

00:06:40.160 --> 00:06:45.530 align:middle line:84%
And actually have two
eigenvalues, say--

00:06:45.530 --> 00:06:53.150 align:middle line:84%
so each u and v have two
independent solutions.

00:06:53.150 --> 00:06:55.280 align:middle line:90%
So you find that the--

00:06:55.280 --> 00:07:03.820 align:middle line:84%
say, for example, one solution
is just given by 1, 0, 0, 0.

00:07:03.820 --> 00:07:04.320 align:middle line:90%
u2.

00:07:04.320 --> 00:07:08.000 align:middle line:90%


00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.600 align:middle line:84%
So this-- we all just discussed
at the end of last lecture

00:07:12.600 --> 00:07:13.100 align:middle line:90%
here--

00:07:13.100 --> 00:07:15.425 align:middle line:90%
I'm just trying to remind you.

00:07:15.425 --> 00:07:25.480 align:middle line:90%


00:07:25.480 --> 00:07:27.910 align:middle line:84%
So in this rest
frame, the solutions

00:07:27.910 --> 00:07:30.010 align:middle line:90%
are particularly simple.

00:07:30.010 --> 00:07:33.370 align:middle line:84%
And so essentially, you have
two independent solutions.

00:07:33.370 --> 00:07:36.035 align:middle line:84%
And then you take and
take actually arbitrary

00:07:36.035 --> 00:07:37.660 align:middle line:84%
linear superposition
of them because we

00:07:37.660 --> 00:07:39.400 align:middle line:90%
are solving linear equations--

00:07:39.400 --> 00:07:41.620 align:middle line:84%
similarly for v.
And you can take

00:07:41.620 --> 00:07:44.080 align:middle line:84%
the arbitrary linear
superposition of these

00:07:44.080 --> 00:07:47.145 align:middle line:90%
and then you will solve them.

00:07:47.145 --> 00:07:50.450 align:middle line:90%


00:07:50.450 --> 00:07:58.330 align:middle line:84%
And then for general
uk and vk, you

00:07:58.330 --> 00:08:01.520 align:middle line:84%
can just perform a
Lorentz transformation.

00:08:01.520 --> 00:08:03.610 align:middle line:84%
So you can perform
Lorentz transformation.

00:08:03.610 --> 00:08:20.020 align:middle line:84%
Say, the uk is obtained by
S lambda uk 0 u0 and vk is

00:08:20.020 --> 00:08:22.650 align:middle line:90%
given by S lambda v0.

00:08:22.650 --> 00:08:26.150 align:middle line:90%


00:08:26.150 --> 00:08:29.330 align:middle line:84%
So the lambda-- so remember,
our notation, S lambda,

00:08:29.330 --> 00:08:32.284 align:middle line:84%
is a Lorentz transformation
on the spinors.

00:08:32.284 --> 00:08:34.159 align:middle line:84%
So the Lorentz transformation
on the spinors.

00:08:34.159 --> 00:08:35.690 align:middle line:84%
And the lambda is
just determined

00:08:35.690 --> 00:08:46.790 align:middle line:84%
by the Lorentz transformation
to take this k0 to k.

00:08:46.790 --> 00:08:51.060 align:middle line:84%
So for arbitrary--
so we take k0,

00:08:51.060 --> 00:08:53.700 align:middle line:84%
so we make the Lorentz
transformation to k,

00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:56.940 align:middle line:90%
and then the corresponding uk.

00:08:56.940 --> 00:08:59.670 align:middle line:90%
Then, it's getting by that.

00:08:59.670 --> 00:09:04.340 align:middle line:90%


00:09:04.340 --> 00:09:09.130 align:middle line:84%
But in practice, if I give
you an arbitrary, say--

00:09:09.130 --> 00:09:14.590 align:middle line:84%
yeah, give you arbitrary k, and
you first work out the lambda,

00:09:14.590 --> 00:09:17.380 align:middle line:84%
then you have to work
out this S lambda.

00:09:17.380 --> 00:09:23.200 align:middle line:84%
So working s lambda is possible,
but again, takes some effort.

00:09:23.200 --> 00:09:26.080 align:middle line:84%
But there's still
a lot of shortcut.

00:09:26.080 --> 00:09:27.590 align:middle line:84%
We can actually
find the solution.

00:09:27.590 --> 00:09:30.535 align:middle line:84%
So this is one way to do it,
and there's alternative way.

00:09:30.535 --> 00:09:39.987 align:middle line:90%


00:09:39.987 --> 00:09:41.820 align:middle line:84%
So before I talk about
this alternative way,

00:09:41.820 --> 00:09:43.050 align:middle line:90%
do you have any questions?

00:09:43.050 --> 00:09:46.020 align:middle line:84%
So this is more or
less where we stopped--

00:09:46.020 --> 00:09:48.285 align:middle line:84%
so at the end of--
before the break.

00:09:48.285 --> 00:09:53.070 align:middle line:90%


00:09:53.070 --> 00:09:56.240 align:middle line:90%
Any questions?

00:09:56.240 --> 00:09:57.980 align:middle line:90%
OK, good.

00:09:57.980 --> 00:10:02.635 align:middle line:84%
So alternatively, we can
actually find a simpler way.

00:10:02.635 --> 00:10:06.540 align:middle line:90%


00:10:06.540 --> 00:10:12.160 align:middle line:84%
So the simpler way is by
observing an identity--

00:10:12.160 --> 00:10:14.800 align:middle line:90%


00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:17.950 align:middle line:84%
you say, if you look
at the k slash square--

00:10:17.950 --> 00:10:22.240 align:middle line:84%
so you have done something
similar in your pset--

00:10:22.240 --> 00:10:24.940 align:middle line:84%
if you look at the
k slash square--

00:10:24.940 --> 00:10:32.110 align:middle line:84%
so this quantity, by definition,
is k mu gamma mu k nu gamma

00:10:32.110 --> 00:10:36.780 align:middle line:84%
nu And then you use the
properties of gamma mu

00:10:36.780 --> 00:10:42.000 align:middle line:84%
and gamma nu, and then you
can easily convince yourself

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:45.800 align:middle line:84%
this is just giving
you the k squared.

00:10:45.800 --> 00:10:47.570 align:middle line:84%
This just gives
you the k square.

00:10:47.570 --> 00:10:52.380 align:middle line:84%
And then-- because we are
looking at on-shell solution,

00:10:52.380 --> 00:10:54.650 align:middle line:84%
so this is just equal
to minus m squared.

00:10:54.650 --> 00:10:59.470 align:middle line:90%


00:10:59.470 --> 00:11:07.250 align:middle line:84%
Then, this means that if
I have ik slash plus m--

00:11:07.250 --> 00:11:09.980 align:middle line:90%


00:11:09.980 --> 00:11:13.740 align:middle line:84%
which-- so up here in
the equation for u and v

00:11:13.740 --> 00:11:16.940 align:middle line:90%
are plus or minus m.

00:11:16.940 --> 00:11:21.050 align:middle line:84%
And then if I multiply
by i k slash minus m--

00:11:21.050 --> 00:11:24.160 align:middle line:90%


00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:29.560 align:middle line:84%
and then essentially I have
minus k slash square minus m

00:11:29.560 --> 00:11:35.630 align:middle line:84%
square, and this is
actually equal to 0

00:11:35.630 --> 00:11:36.785 align:middle line:90%
because of this equation.

00:11:36.785 --> 00:11:44.520 align:middle line:90%


00:11:44.520 --> 00:11:46.320 align:middle line:84%
So now we can
immediately observe--

00:11:46.320 --> 00:11:48.860 align:middle line:90%


00:11:48.860 --> 00:11:54.720 align:middle line:84%
so now, we can immediately
observe if I take a solution--

00:11:54.720 --> 00:11:58.200 align:middle line:90%


00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:04.630 align:middle line:84%
if I just-- to
solve that equation,

00:12:04.630 --> 00:12:15.640 align:middle line:84%
you can just write u as say
some normalization constant--

00:12:15.640 --> 00:12:18.504 align:middle line:84%
N will be a normalization
constant-- and i k

00:12:18.504 --> 00:12:20.080 align:middle line:90%
slash plus m.

00:12:20.080 --> 00:12:23.230 align:middle line:90%


00:12:23.230 --> 00:12:29.500 align:middle line:84%
And then they're acting on
some arbitrary u tilde--

00:12:29.500 --> 00:12:30.850 align:middle line:90%
some arbitrary spinor.

00:12:30.850 --> 00:12:32.710 align:middle line:90%
And then this equation--

00:12:32.710 --> 00:12:34.840 align:middle line:84%
that equation
automatically satisfies.

00:12:34.840 --> 00:12:37.380 align:middle line:90%


00:12:37.380 --> 00:12:44.370 align:middle line:84%
And similarly, v, if I take
some normalization constant,

00:12:44.370 --> 00:12:49.500 align:middle line:84%
and I take minus
i k slash plus m--

00:12:49.500 --> 00:12:52.590 align:middle line:90%
say some v tilde--

00:12:52.590 --> 00:12:55.740 align:middle line:84%
so that equation, again,
automatically-- the v equation

00:12:55.740 --> 00:13:00.010 align:middle line:84%
automatically satisfied
because of this identity.

00:13:00.010 --> 00:13:02.440 align:middle line:84%
And now, we know
that there's only two

00:13:02.440 --> 00:13:04.120 align:middle line:90%
independent equations--

00:13:04.120 --> 00:13:11.210 align:middle line:84%
two independent solutions
for both u and v,

00:13:11.210 --> 00:13:15.420 align:middle line:90%
so we can choose a basis for u.

00:13:15.420 --> 00:13:19.035 align:middle line:84%
And just by taking
this to be, say, us 0--

00:13:19.035 --> 00:13:25.730 align:middle line:90%


00:13:25.730 --> 00:13:28.340 align:middle line:90%
and then this would be a basis--

00:13:28.340 --> 00:13:30.400 align:middle line:90%
a complete basis of solutions.

00:13:30.400 --> 00:13:34.000 align:middle line:90%
So s would go 1 to 2.

00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:35.890 align:middle line:84%
So because we have--
and for each of them,

00:13:35.890 --> 00:13:37.720 align:middle line:84%
we have two
independent solutions.

00:13:37.720 --> 00:13:40.910 align:middle line:90%


00:13:40.910 --> 00:13:43.850 align:middle line:84%
And so the reason we
can choose us here--

00:13:43.850 --> 00:13:47.270 align:middle line:84%
you can also check that
when you take the m--

00:13:47.270 --> 00:13:49.580 align:middle line:90%
when you take the to be--

00:13:49.580 --> 00:13:54.050 align:middle line:84%
yeah, so when you
take k to be k0--

00:13:54.050 --> 00:13:57.350 align:middle line:84%
so you can easily check
yourself that this equation--

00:13:57.350 --> 00:14:02.800 align:middle line:84%
this essentially just
reduced to a us 0.

00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:04.480 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, this is consistent--

00:14:04.480 --> 00:14:07.150 align:middle line:90%
just say when you take that--

00:14:07.150 --> 00:14:08.590 align:middle line:90%
you just reduce to this basis.

00:14:08.590 --> 00:14:11.830 align:middle line:90%


00:14:11.830 --> 00:14:13.780 align:middle line:84%
So n is a
normalization constant.

00:14:13.780 --> 00:14:26.270 align:middle line:90%


00:14:26.270 --> 00:14:33.820 align:middle line:84%
And so the us vs then
provides a basis--

00:14:33.820 --> 00:14:35.740 align:middle line:84%
then this is a
basis of solutions.

00:14:35.740 --> 00:14:45.220 align:middle line:90%


00:14:45.220 --> 00:14:47.710 align:middle line:84%
And we can be sure these
are the complete basis

00:14:47.710 --> 00:14:50.890 align:middle line:90%
because that's the only--

00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:56.110 align:middle line:84%
yeah, essentially, we already
know the solution at the rest

00:14:56.110 --> 00:14:59.710 align:middle line:84%
frame, and we just
have the right number

00:14:59.710 --> 00:15:02.080 align:middle line:90%
of the independent solutions.

00:15:02.080 --> 00:15:03.087 align:middle line:90%
Yes?

00:15:03.087 --> 00:15:05.170 align:middle line:84%
STUDENT: How do we know
the normalization constant

00:15:05.170 --> 00:15:07.090 align:middle line:90%
is the same for uv?

00:15:07.090 --> 00:15:11.800 align:middle line:84%
PROFESSOR: Oh, yeah,
here, we don't know.

00:15:11.800 --> 00:15:14.390 align:middle line:84%
But you can guess why
it should be the same.

00:15:14.390 --> 00:15:18.820 align:middle line:84%
It's just essentially--
so this u-- yeah,

00:15:18.820 --> 00:15:21.040 align:middle line:84%
because the equation
looks pretty symmetric

00:15:21.040 --> 00:15:24.160 align:middle line:84%
and the normalization constant
don't depend on the sign of m,

00:15:24.160 --> 00:15:25.060 align:middle line:90%
essentially.

00:15:25.060 --> 00:15:28.340 align:middle line:90%


00:15:28.340 --> 00:15:31.910 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, in principle, I
should write in 1 and 2.

00:15:31.910 --> 00:15:37.460 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, just-- but in the
end, they are the same.

00:15:37.460 --> 00:15:38.040 align:middle line:90%
Good.

00:15:38.040 --> 00:15:39.920 align:middle line:90%
Any other questions?

00:15:39.920 --> 00:15:44.070 align:middle line:90%


00:15:44.070 --> 00:15:47.220 align:middle line:90%
So you can also--

00:15:47.220 --> 00:15:51.150 align:middle line:84%
yeah, if you take the conjugate,
then you can get the--

00:15:51.150 --> 00:15:57.000 align:middle line:84%
what's the u dagger or the
u bar or v dagger v bar.

00:15:57.000 --> 00:16:00.790 align:middle line:84%
So for example, you
just take the conjugate,

00:16:00.790 --> 00:16:03.460 align:middle line:90%
then you find the us bar.

00:16:03.460 --> 00:16:07.380 align:middle line:84%
So I hope you still remember
the notation-- the us bar--

00:16:07.380 --> 00:16:12.390 align:middle line:84%
which is the us dagger times
gamma 0 and the us bar--

00:16:12.390 --> 00:16:16.590 align:middle line:84%
so this is for the conjugate
solution-- will be an--

00:16:16.590 --> 00:16:17.370 align:middle line:90%
the same n.

00:16:17.370 --> 00:16:18.900 align:middle line:90%
We can take n to be real--

00:16:18.900 --> 00:16:25.830 align:middle line:84%
say, us bar 0, then
i k slash plus m.

00:16:25.830 --> 00:16:29.310 align:middle line:84%
So you just use the
properties of the--

00:16:29.310 --> 00:16:43.250 align:middle line:90%


00:16:43.250 --> 00:16:44.510 align:middle line:90%
so you can also find this.

00:16:44.510 --> 00:16:47.530 align:middle line:90%


00:16:47.530 --> 00:16:50.820 align:middle line:84%
So now you can easily
check yourself again using

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:53.540 align:middle line:90%
this equation--

00:16:53.540 --> 00:16:57.440 align:middle line:84%
you can check that the
u bar and the v bar

00:16:57.440 --> 00:16:59.900 align:middle line:84%
are actually-- u
and v are orthogonal

00:16:59.900 --> 00:17:01.260 align:middle line:90%
in the following sense.

00:17:01.260 --> 00:17:09.140 align:middle line:84%
And ur bar vs is
equal to v bar r us

00:17:09.140 --> 00:17:15.680 align:middle line:84%
is equal to 0 for arbitrary
r, s equal to 1 and 2.

00:17:15.680 --> 00:17:17.540 align:middle line:90%
So u and v are orthogonal.

00:17:17.540 --> 00:17:24.630 align:middle line:90%


00:17:24.630 --> 00:17:27.200 align:middle line:90%
And we can also --

00:17:27.200 --> 00:17:32.180 align:middle line:84%
and then we need to fix the
normalization of u and v.

00:17:32.180 --> 00:17:36.690 align:middle line:84%
So it's convenient to fix
the normalization as follows.

00:17:36.690 --> 00:17:39.320 align:middle line:84%
So we will use the
following convention--

00:17:39.320 --> 00:17:44.240 align:middle line:90%
say us bar k--

00:17:44.240 --> 00:17:56.510 align:middle line:84%
say, ur k u bar and us k
equal to i 2 m delta rs.

00:17:56.510 --> 00:18:05.965 align:middle line:84%
And similarly, vr bar
k and vs k - i 2m.

00:18:05.965 --> 00:18:17.790 align:middle line:90%


00:18:17.790 --> 00:18:21.150 align:middle line:84%
So these 2m just
for convenience.

00:18:21.150 --> 00:18:24.600 align:middle line:84%
So it just convention
for convenience.

00:18:24.600 --> 00:18:32.900 align:middle line:84%
And so you can check
yourself that actually--

00:18:32.900 --> 00:18:37.676 align:middle line:90%
yeah, so different u--

00:18:37.676 --> 00:18:39.540 align:middle line:84%
different value of
r and s, they're

00:18:39.540 --> 00:18:40.790 align:middle line:90%
also orthogonal to each other.

00:18:40.790 --> 00:18:45.020 align:middle line:84%
You can already see
already in the rest frame.

00:18:45.020 --> 00:18:47.960 align:middle line:84%
You can just easily check
using those expressions,

00:18:47.960 --> 00:18:51.305 align:middle line:84%
but you can also check
again using this identity

00:18:51.305 --> 00:18:53.510 align:middle line:84%
that the different
value of r and s,

00:18:53.510 --> 00:18:55.110 align:middle line:84%
they are orthogonal
to each other.

00:18:55.110 --> 00:18:57.410 align:middle line:84%
And when they are
the same, and then we

00:18:57.410 --> 00:19:02.620 align:middle line:84%
normalize the
constant to be 2 m.

00:19:02.620 --> 00:19:07.300 align:middle line:84%
And from here, you
can deduce that N

00:19:07.300 --> 00:19:13.850 align:middle line:84%
is equal to 1 over square
root E plus M. So from now on,

00:19:13.850 --> 00:19:17.230 align:middle line:84%
I will also use
this notation for E.

00:19:17.230 --> 00:19:22.630 align:middle line:84%
So the E-- the
energy is omega k.

00:19:22.630 --> 00:19:25.135 align:middle line:84%
So now, I will also
use this notation.

00:19:25.135 --> 00:19:37.970 align:middle line:90%


00:19:37.970 --> 00:19:38.540 align:middle line:90%
Good.

00:19:38.540 --> 00:19:42.010 align:middle line:84%
So this gives you
a complete basis

00:19:42.010 --> 00:19:46.240 align:middle line:84%
of solutions to the
Dirac equations.

00:19:46.240 --> 00:19:48.430 align:middle line:84%
So now, let me just
write them down

00:19:48.430 --> 00:19:51.460 align:middle line:84%
to give you a
little bit intuition

00:19:51.460 --> 00:19:53.420 align:middle line:90%
about the explicit expression.

00:19:53.420 --> 00:19:59.320 align:middle line:84%
So with those gamma matrices,
we can just plug in here.

00:19:59.320 --> 00:20:02.200 align:middle line:90%
And we know what the us 0 vs 0.

00:20:02.200 --> 00:20:06.280 align:middle line:84%
We know n, so in principle, we
can write them down explicitly.

00:20:06.280 --> 00:20:10.270 align:middle line:84%
So you find that in that
basis, then the us k

00:20:10.270 --> 00:20:14.110 align:middle line:90%
is given by the following--

00:20:14.110 --> 00:20:22.730 align:middle line:84%
given by the square
root E plus M xi s,

00:20:22.730 --> 00:20:33.770 align:middle line:84%
and the sigma dot k divided
by square root E plus M xi s.

00:20:33.770 --> 00:20:37.090 align:middle line:90%


00:20:37.090 --> 00:20:49.750 align:middle line:84%
And the vs k is
given by sigma dot

00:20:49.750 --> 00:21:05.500 align:middle line:84%
k divided by square root E plus
M also xi s, and E plus M xi s.

00:21:05.500 --> 00:21:08.210 align:middle line:90%
And xi s is a 2.

00:21:08.210 --> 00:21:13.400 align:middle line:90%
So s from 1 to 2, and xi 1--

00:21:13.400 --> 00:21:16.860 align:middle line:84%
so psi s are two
component vectors.

00:21:16.860 --> 00:21:21.560 align:middle line:84%
One is given by 1, 0, and
the other is given by 0, 1.

00:21:21.560 --> 00:21:28.200 align:middle line:90%


00:21:28.200 --> 00:21:31.250 align:middle line:90%
So that you get--

00:21:31.250 --> 00:21:37.510 align:middle line:84%
so you can see in
the rest frame,

00:21:37.510 --> 00:21:39.940 align:middle line:84%
k equal to 0--
essentially, for u,

00:21:39.940 --> 00:21:45.440 align:middle line:84%
you're just left with the
upper half because this is 0.

00:21:45.440 --> 00:21:49.310 align:middle line:84%
And then we have the
1, 0 and the 0, 1.

00:21:49.310 --> 00:21:51.140 align:middle line:90%
And then when k equal to 0--

00:21:51.140 --> 00:21:53.630 align:middle line:84%
and for v, just left
with a lower half.

00:21:53.630 --> 00:21:57.200 align:middle line:84%
And again, we have
the 1, 0 and the 0, 1.

00:21:57.200 --> 00:22:00.470 align:middle line:84%
So this is consistent
with the rest frame result

00:22:00.470 --> 00:22:03.690 align:middle line:90%
we obtained earlier.

00:22:03.690 --> 00:22:04.190 align:middle line:90%
Good.

00:22:04.190 --> 00:22:05.110 align:middle line:90%
Any questions on this?

00:22:05.110 --> 00:22:05.710 align:middle line:90%
Yes?

00:22:05.710 --> 00:22:07.460 align:middle line:84%
STUDENT: What are the
sig -- what's sigma?

00:22:07.460 --> 00:22:09.890 align:middle line:84%
PROFESSOR: Oh, sigma
just the sigma matrix.

00:22:09.890 --> 00:22:12.790 align:middle line:84%
So this sigma just
Pauli matrices.

00:22:12.790 --> 00:22:15.100 align:middle line:90%
Sigma 1, sigma 2, sigma 3--

00:22:15.100 --> 00:22:15.970 align:middle line:90%
Pauli matrices.

00:22:15.970 --> 00:22:22.974 align:middle line:90%


00:22:22.974 --> 00:22:23.474 align:middle line:90%
Good?

00:22:23.474 --> 00:22:27.910 align:middle line:90%


00:22:27.910 --> 00:22:30.580 align:middle line:90%
So let me just mention a few--

00:22:30.580 --> 00:22:33.820 align:middle line:84%
make a few remarks
on the solutions.

00:22:33.820 --> 00:22:43.870 align:middle line:84%
And to be familiar with the
properties of the solutions

00:22:43.870 --> 00:22:46.690 align:middle line:84%
actually will be very
useful when later you

00:22:46.690 --> 00:22:51.280 align:middle line:84%
do Feynman diagram calculations,
because the different--

00:22:51.280 --> 00:22:56.020 align:middle line:84%
when you involve, say,
electron fermions-- and now,

00:22:56.020 --> 00:22:57.670 align:middle line:90%
it's no longer plane wave.

00:22:57.670 --> 00:23:02.240 align:middle line:84%
So this u and v will enter your
Feynman diagram calculations.

00:23:02.240 --> 00:23:04.420 align:middle line:84%
And if you are familiar
with their properties--

00:23:04.420 --> 00:23:08.830 align:middle line:84%
and will help you to
do such calculations.

00:23:08.830 --> 00:23:12.700 align:middle line:84%
So let me just first
mention some properties.

00:23:12.700 --> 00:23:17.120 align:middle line:90%


00:23:17.120 --> 00:23:19.860 align:middle line:90%
Make some remarks.

00:23:19.860 --> 00:23:23.375 align:middle line:84%
So first is that if we consider
the non-relativistic limit--

00:23:23.375 --> 00:23:27.310 align:middle line:90%


00:23:27.310 --> 00:23:30.250 align:middle line:84%
the non-relativistic limit-- so
that's corresponding to-- you

00:23:30.250 --> 00:23:37.180 align:middle line:84%
take the magnitude of k
divided by m goes to 0.

00:23:37.180 --> 00:23:40.720 align:middle line:84%
And then in this limit, E would
be approximately equal to m.

00:23:40.720 --> 00:23:46.050 align:middle line:90%


00:23:46.050 --> 00:23:47.760 align:middle line:84%
And then you find
the leading order

00:23:47.760 --> 00:23:52.590 align:middle line:84%
when you expand, say, in-- yeah,
so you can expand this in 1

00:23:52.590 --> 00:23:59.540 align:middle line:84%
over M. So the
leading order, you

00:23:59.540 --> 00:24:05.160 align:middle line:84%
find that the us k-- so you
can just easily do these two.

00:24:05.160 --> 00:24:08.670 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, so this
term, certainly, you

00:24:08.670 --> 00:24:10.410 align:middle line:90%
can just ignore because E--

00:24:10.410 --> 00:24:12.450 align:middle line:90%
so this is M--

00:24:12.450 --> 00:24:15.000 align:middle line:84%
so this is k divided
by square root of M,

00:24:15.000 --> 00:24:17.380 align:middle line:84%
so this is higher
order than this one.

00:24:17.380 --> 00:24:19.110 align:middle line:84%
And here, it's the
square root of M.

00:24:19.110 --> 00:24:28.250 align:middle line:84%
So to leading order, you
have square root 2m xi s 0.

00:24:28.250 --> 00:24:37.030 align:middle line:84%
Similarly, vs k equal to
square root of 2m leading order

00:24:37.030 --> 00:24:38.770 align:middle line:90%
0 xi s.

00:24:38.770 --> 00:24:45.490 align:middle line:90%


00:24:45.490 --> 00:24:53.540 align:middle line:84%
So essentially, what you see
in the non-relativistic limit--

00:24:53.540 --> 00:24:57.150 align:middle line:84%
for example, if we look at this
positive energy solutions--

00:24:57.150 --> 00:25:01.470 align:middle line:84%
so this just reduced
to arbitrary--

00:25:01.470 --> 00:25:06.660 align:middle line:84%
so us k-- yeah, now you can
do linear superposition--

00:25:06.660 --> 00:25:22.520 align:middle line:84%
just uk just reduce to arbitrary
two component complex vector.

00:25:22.520 --> 00:25:30.580 align:middle line:90%


00:25:30.580 --> 00:25:32.590 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, so you just--

00:25:32.590 --> 00:25:34.450 align:middle line:90%
so this is just some constant.

00:25:34.450 --> 00:25:36.820 align:middle line:84%
And as a basis, you
just have this basis,

00:25:36.820 --> 00:25:39.820 align:middle line:84%
and then you can just
now do arbitrary-- yeah,

00:25:39.820 --> 00:25:42.920 align:middle line:84%
just become the
arbitrary complex vector.

00:25:42.920 --> 00:25:49.900 align:middle line:84%
So the should remind you how we
describe a spin-half particle

00:25:49.900 --> 00:25:51.670 align:middle line:90%
in non-relativistic limit.

00:25:51.670 --> 00:25:55.510 align:middle line:84%
In the non-relativistic
limit, the way

00:25:55.510 --> 00:25:58.720 align:middle line:84%
we describe the
spin-half particle--

00:25:58.720 --> 00:26:02.920 align:middle line:84%
and it's precisely a
two-component vector.

00:26:02.920 --> 00:26:18.310 align:middle line:84%
So so this is exactly
as the description

00:26:18.310 --> 00:26:23.705 align:middle line:90%
of a spin-half particle.

00:26:23.705 --> 00:26:26.450 align:middle line:90%


00:26:26.450 --> 00:26:29.480 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, the wave function--

00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:30.950 align:middle line:84%
yeah, here, you
should understand

00:26:30.950 --> 00:26:33.290 align:middle line:84%
this-- the wave
function description

00:26:33.290 --> 00:26:37.610 align:middle line:84%
of the spin-half particle
in non-relativistic quantum

00:26:37.610 --> 00:26:38.240 align:middle line:90%
mechanics.

00:26:38.240 --> 00:26:42.840 align:middle line:90%


00:26:42.840 --> 00:26:44.670 align:middle line:84%
And as I will not
go through here,

00:26:44.670 --> 00:26:51.360 align:middle line:84%
but you can show in the
non-relativistic limit,

00:26:51.360 --> 00:26:54.815 align:middle line:84%
this solution
actually decouples.

00:26:54.815 --> 00:26:56.690 align:middle line:84%
In the end, when you
solve the equation, only

00:26:56.690 --> 00:26:58.640 align:middle line:90%
one half of the equation--

00:26:58.640 --> 00:27:01.400 align:middle line:84%
one half of the
solution remains.

00:27:01.400 --> 00:27:04.474 align:middle line:84%
And actually, this
is no longer--

00:27:04.474 --> 00:27:08.130 align:middle line:84%
it just gets the
positive energy solution.

00:27:08.130 --> 00:27:11.900 align:middle line:84%
So in that limit,
you essentially only

00:27:11.900 --> 00:27:13.460 align:middle line:90%
reduce to two components.

00:27:13.460 --> 00:27:20.960 align:middle line:90%


00:27:20.960 --> 00:27:22.700 align:middle line:90%
So this is the first remark.

00:27:22.700 --> 00:27:27.640 align:middle line:84%
So this is the first indication
we see that this should likely

00:27:27.640 --> 00:27:30.580 align:middle line:90%
describe a spin-half particle.

00:27:30.580 --> 00:27:35.275 align:middle line:84%
The Dirac theory likely
describes a spin-half particle.

00:27:35.275 --> 00:27:38.820 align:middle line:90%


00:27:38.820 --> 00:27:44.880 align:middle line:84%
So the second limit
we can consider

00:27:44.880 --> 00:27:47.685 align:middle line:84%
is considered the ultra
relativistic limit.

00:27:47.685 --> 00:27:59.070 align:middle line:90%


00:27:59.070 --> 00:28:04.020 align:middle line:84%
So this is a limit which
E is much greater than--

00:28:04.020 --> 00:28:08.130 align:middle line:84%
energy is much greater
than M. And E then

00:28:08.130 --> 00:28:13.665 align:middle line:84%
will be approximate, say, to
k-- to the magnitude of k.

00:28:13.665 --> 00:28:16.310 align:middle line:90%


00:28:16.310 --> 00:28:19.010 align:middle line:84%
And now let's also
define the direction of k

00:28:19.010 --> 00:28:26.150 align:middle line:84%
by just k divided
by its magnitude.

00:28:26.150 --> 00:28:30.590 align:middle line:84%
So we also introduced the
k hat is the unit vector

00:28:30.590 --> 00:28:32.000 align:middle line:90%
along the direction of the k.

00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:37.390 align:middle line:84%
So in this case, you can
do a small m expansion--

00:28:37.390 --> 00:28:41.890 align:middle line:84%
just do a small expansion--
this expression for u and v.

00:28:41.890 --> 00:28:46.510 align:middle line:84%
And then you find
the leading order--

00:28:46.510 --> 00:28:52.500 align:middle line:90%
us k given by square root of E.

00:28:52.500 --> 00:29:02.590 align:middle line:84%
And then you have xi s, and
then you have sigma k hat xi s.

00:29:02.590 --> 00:29:04.850 align:middle line:90%
This is for the us.

00:29:04.850 --> 00:29:06.470 align:middle line:90%
And for the vs, you find--

00:29:06.470 --> 00:29:24.090 align:middle line:90%


00:29:24.090 --> 00:29:27.790 align:middle line:84%
so that's the-- so you find
that solution simplify,

00:29:27.790 --> 00:29:30.480 align:middle line:84%
and so that's the
result you get.

00:29:30.480 --> 00:29:36.330 align:middle line:90%


00:29:36.330 --> 00:29:43.020 align:middle line:84%
So it's not manifest
from this expression,

00:29:43.020 --> 00:29:49.960 align:middle line:84%
but actually, there's something
very special in this simplified

00:29:49.960 --> 00:29:52.580 align:middle line:84%
expression in the ultra
relativistic limit.

00:29:52.580 --> 00:29:55.970 align:middle line:90%
So if you look at--

00:29:55.970 --> 00:29:59.120 align:middle line:90%
so the expression for u and v--

00:29:59.120 --> 00:30:03.140 align:middle line:84%
these are linearly independent,
in the sense that no matter how

00:30:03.140 --> 00:30:05.240 align:middle line:84%
you do linear
superposition of u,

00:30:05.240 --> 00:30:07.310 align:middle line:90%
you will not be able to get v.

00:30:07.310 --> 00:30:09.950 align:middle line:84%
And also how you do
linear superposition of v,

00:30:09.950 --> 00:30:13.010 align:middle line:90%
you won't get u.

00:30:13.010 --> 00:30:16.310 align:middle line:84%
But in this limit, even
though it's not clear--

00:30:16.310 --> 00:30:19.110 align:middle line:84%
not manifest in this
form, but in fact,

00:30:19.110 --> 00:30:23.480 align:middle line:84%
these two are linearly
related to each other.

00:30:23.480 --> 00:30:27.390 align:middle line:90%
So this can be seen as follows.

00:30:27.390 --> 00:30:46.660 align:middle line:84%
So if you use the identity
that's sigma dot k square--

00:30:46.660 --> 00:30:51.610 align:middle line:84%
so this is the analog of
this equation for the sigma

00:30:51.610 --> 00:30:52.600 align:middle line:90%
matrices--

00:30:52.600 --> 00:30:54.460 align:middle line:90%
for the Pauli matrices.

00:30:54.460 --> 00:30:56.350 align:middle line:84%
And this, you can
easily-- again,

00:30:56.350 --> 00:30:58.000 align:middle line:84%
using the property
of Pauli matrices,

00:30:58.000 --> 00:31:00.880 align:middle line:84%
you can convince yourself
that this is just

00:31:00.880 --> 00:31:02.410 align:middle line:90%
giving you k hat squared.

00:31:02.410 --> 00:31:05.440 align:middle line:90%


00:31:05.440 --> 00:31:07.060 align:middle line:90%
And this is actually--

00:31:07.060 --> 00:31:10.540 align:middle line:84%
because this is unit
vector, this is just 1.

00:31:10.540 --> 00:31:16.440 align:middle line:84%
So now, if you use this
property, this is equal to 1.

00:31:16.440 --> 00:31:18.480 align:middle line:90%
And then we find--

00:31:18.480 --> 00:31:25.800 align:middle line:84%
and then let eta s
equal to sigma k--

00:31:25.800 --> 00:31:30.600 align:middle line:90%
sigma dot k hat xi s.

00:31:30.600 --> 00:31:35.250 align:middle line:84%
And then you find that
the vs k can be written

00:31:35.250 --> 00:31:37.110 align:middle line:90%
in the exact form as us k.

00:31:37.110 --> 00:31:39.630 align:middle line:90%
You just replace eta s by--

00:31:39.630 --> 00:31:41.010 align:middle line:90%
xi s by eta s.

00:31:41.010 --> 00:31:45.600 align:middle line:84%
And then you can have it
in the following form--

00:31:45.600 --> 00:31:56.840 align:middle line:84%
square root E eta s
sigma dot k eta s.

00:31:56.840 --> 00:31:59.270 align:middle line:84%
So obviously, this
is equivalent to that

00:31:59.270 --> 00:32:03.050 align:middle line:84%
once you plug in the eta
s equal to sigma k psi s,

00:32:03.050 --> 00:32:05.660 align:middle line:84%
because this just
gives you that.

00:32:05.660 --> 00:32:08.720 align:middle line:84%
And when you plug in to here,
you get the sigma k square,

00:32:08.720 --> 00:32:11.390 align:middle line:84%
and you get 1, and again,
you reduce to that.

00:32:11.390 --> 00:32:14.380 align:middle line:90%


00:32:14.380 --> 00:32:23.530 align:middle line:84%
But now, this have exactly
the same form as this one,

00:32:23.530 --> 00:32:29.980 align:middle line:84%
except now eta s is a linear
superposition of the xi s.

00:32:29.980 --> 00:32:36.480 align:middle line:84%
Then that means that the vs is a
linear superposition of the us.

00:32:36.480 --> 00:32:43.870 align:middle line:84%
So this means that the vs is
a linear superposition of vs.

00:32:43.870 --> 00:32:59.980 align:middle line:84%
So vs now is a linear
superposition of vs-- of us.

00:32:59.980 --> 00:33:02.200 align:middle line:84%
So they are no
longer independent,

00:33:02.200 --> 00:33:10.690 align:middle line:84%
so they are not
