this may not appear a surprise

00:33:27.970 --> 00:33:31.150 align:middle line:84%
to you, because
previously, we already

00:33:31.150 --> 00:33:36.400 align:middle line:84%
discussed when we derive
the Dirac equation.

00:33:36.400 --> 00:33:39.900 align:middle line:84%
So Dirac equation--
in order to satisfy

00:33:39.900 --> 00:33:43.590 align:middle line:84%
all the properties
for non-zero M,

00:33:43.590 --> 00:33:47.940 align:middle line:84%
we need four
dimensional matrices.

00:33:47.940 --> 00:33:50.970 align:middle line:84%
So that means psi
is a four vector.

00:33:50.970 --> 00:33:55.490 align:middle line:84%
But we also mentioned that
if you in the massless case

00:33:55.490 --> 00:33:57.670 align:middle line:90%
set m equal to 0--

00:33:57.670 --> 00:33:59.350 align:middle line:84%
in the massless
case, actually, you

00:33:59.350 --> 00:34:03.470 align:middle line:84%
can use two components--
just use gamma matrices.

00:34:03.470 --> 00:34:06.520 align:middle line:84%
So that means that if you solve
a massless Dirac equation,

00:34:06.520 --> 00:34:10.150 align:middle line:84%
you only need-- you only have
two independent solutions.

00:34:10.150 --> 00:34:12.790 align:middle line:84%
And this ultrarelativistic
limit is precisely

00:34:12.790 --> 00:34:14.980 align:middle line:84%
like the massless limit
because the mass--

00:34:14.980 --> 00:34:16.960 align:middle line:84%
the energy is much
greater than the mass,

00:34:16.960 --> 00:34:20.800 align:middle line:84%
and then you can neglect
the effect of mass.

00:34:20.800 --> 00:34:22.360 align:middle line:90%
So this is consistent--

00:34:22.360 --> 00:34:26.489 align:middle line:90%


00:34:26.489 --> 00:34:43.080 align:middle line:84%
with that the massless Dirac
equation consistent with that--

00:34:43.080 --> 00:34:55.750 align:middle line:84%
only requires two components
rather than four components.

00:34:55.750 --> 00:34:59.510 align:middle line:90%


00:34:59.510 --> 00:35:00.603 align:middle line:90%
Yes?

00:35:00.603 --> 00:35:02.395 align:middle line:84%
STUDENT: So in the
